From $\mathbf{a} \times (\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{b}) = \mathbf{c},$
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{a} (\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b}) - \mathbf{b} (\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{a}) &= \mathbf{c} \\
\mathbf{a} (\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b}) &= \mathbf{b} - \mathbf{c}.
\end{align*}Taking magnitudes, we get
\[\|\mathbf{a} (\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b})\| = \|\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{c}\|.\]Then
\[|\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b}| = \|\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{c}\|.\]Since $\|\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{c}\| = 2,$ $|\mathbf{a} \cdot \mathbf{b}| = 2.$

